						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In EQ1 there were no ^ or ^^ or ^^^ mobs... it was all just colors..
<br />

<br />
When you solo'd you solo'd mobs that were green, blue... maybe white... when you grouped you went after oranges and reds.
<br />

<br />
When you wanted to go solo... you simply walked back to the zone your normal exp group left last week because you out leveled it as a group... and solo'd it.
<br />

<br />
I don't see that much of a flaw with that system... except for the way stats work now.
<br />

<br />
In EQ1 it was harder to completely trivialize content... in EQ2 I simply had to be 50... sing my right songs and I was invulnerable to lvl 45 and 46 mobs.... if they leave +DEF outta the game that means lvl 42 mobs will have a rough time hitting me.
<br />

<br />
The reason I bring this up is that the easiest fix would seem to be remove solo content... make all content... just CONTENT... and then widen the "con range" so that green goes deeper down... but do to the fact they *wanted* 42's to have a really rough time hitting you this means you could get exp risk free if a 42 was green... 
<br />

<br />
So that's the dilema really... it at first seems like an easy solution... remove solo content and widen the con ranges... but the combat engine is not able to handle that in a balanced manner....<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.thedauntless.org" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://tinyurl.com/6qjqw/blah.png" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
				</tr>
