							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hmm.  I do admire the simplicity of the EQ1 system but to say you don't see much of a flaw?
<br />

<br />
If you ever watched an enchanter soloing in Tactics or HOH or watched a bard cleaning out Maiden's Eye, it would be very hard to defend the system as unflawed when talking to, say, a rogue who never earned a single point of XP after level 30 or so without having at least part of a group with him.
<br />

<br />
I vastly prefer having clearly labelled solo versus group content over a system where one class could gain 2 AA points per hour while others were lucky to get 2 a week.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.mausturm.com/EQ2/images/dingsig1.jpg"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
