							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">See there is the problem though.  In every word you post it's obvious that you have a disdain for grouping and it shows in your ideas.
<br />

<br />
As I said, I personally solo (2 box) quite often.  I have no disdain for it at all and actually do it sometimes even when I have the time to group.  But, I realize that in a Massive Multiplayer Online Roleplaying Game the point is to interact with other people.  
<br />

<br />
Really though, where are you forced to group anymore?  On the Isle you have to group to do the Orc, if you want to do him.  In the cities everything is solo based including your class quests.  Sure when you get to your AQs they are group based, but again you don't have to do them.  Even roadblocks to the solo player like the access quests to Zek/EL+ are gone now instead of even just having the level limit that existed.  
<br />

<br />
The solo player is not blocked from any content except the content which they aren't willing to use by grouping.  If you want to solo from the Isle to Everfrost so be it.  You'll get there, but you aren't going to have as easy a time as somebody who has worked with others to do it.  It's just how it is.
<br />

<br />
The problem with your idea is that you want high fantasy.  You want to be that lone warrior that walks into a room and downs a dragon after a drawn out fight.  Except that high fantasy just doesn't work in a game of this size.  Everybody can't have soloed dragons or old dark gods.  Instead you base it on a team concept so that when you do kill these beings, complete these quests, or whatever else it comes as something to be proud of.
<br />

<br />
I really suggest that if that is the game you want, you go and find a nice RPG for your computer instead.  Morrowwind is supposedly a great game for example.  You have all the options you want and in the end you get to be the guy who saves the day by your lonesome.  Or even just find another MMORPG that is more suited to your playstyle.  EQ2 will be based around group content for it's lifetime and you'll just end up disapointed by the choices you make in denying yourself group content.
<br />

<br />
Weep,
<br />
A Dirge on Kithicor</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
